3cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195444/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-8-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-8\" data-attachment-id=\"653187\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195444/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-8.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195444/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-8-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe 1984 Maxi Turbo represented the pinnacle of this rally beast, sporting a wider, lighter frame and a manic 345hp from its 1.5-litre engine. It must have been a riot to drive, even if it wasn’t a championship contender.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195516/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-16.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195516/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-16-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-16\" data-attachment-id=\"653195\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195516/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-16.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-16/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195516/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-16-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAfter the road-going R5 Turbo 2 ceased production in 1986, Renault struggled to maintain its performance image. To spice things up, the French automaker introduced the Renault Sport Spider. I’m glad it did – I absolutely \u003cem\u003eadore\u003c/em\u003e this car.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195452/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-10.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195452/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-10-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-10\" data-attachment-id=\"653189\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195452/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-10.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-10/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195452/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-10-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Spider boasts a simplistic beauty absent in many track-day specials: soft curves, a low nose, and pretty headlights. The rear end is a bit awkward, with taillights seemingly lost in space, yet the proportions are fantastic.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195422/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-3-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-3\" data-attachment-id=\"653182\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195422/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-3.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-3/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195422/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-3-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195456/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-11-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-11\" data-attachment-id=\"653190\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195456/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-11.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-11/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195456/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-11-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195427/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-4-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-4\" data-attachment-id=\"653183\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195427/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-4.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-4/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195427/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-4-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eBritish models featured a glass windscreen, but European versions had the option of a literal ‘windscreen’ – a ducted scoop that directed air up and away from the cockpit – ingenious!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195417/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-2-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-2\" data-attachment-id=\"653181\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195417/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-2.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195417/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-2-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195508/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-14-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-14\" data-attachment-id=\"653193\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195508/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-14.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-14/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195508/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-14-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195500/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-12-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-12\" data-attachment-id=\"653191\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195500/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-12.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-12/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195500/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-12-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003ePowered by a 2.0 inline-four from the Renault Clio Williams, the 930kg Spider matched the 5 Turbo’s 0-60mph time of 6.9 seconds, delivering a fun yet manageable driving experience. My favourite detail? The butterfly doors, or, in this car’s case… the ‘baguette holder.’ \u003cem\u003eTrés bon!\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063334/MC-SS-Pairs-SH.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063334/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH\" data-attachment-id=\"653241\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063334/MC-SS-Pairs-SH.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063334/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe 5 Turbo was over twice as expensive a Volkswagen Golf GTI when new, and it was produced in limited numbers. The Spider, meanwhile, started at nearly £30,000 (approximately US$39,000 in today’s money) – £7,000 (US$9,100) more than a Lotus Elise at the time. Practicality wasn’t the Spider’s strong suit either.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195623/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-32.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195623/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-32-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-32\" data-attachment-id=\"653211\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195623/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-32.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-32/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195623/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-32-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195544/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-23.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195544/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-23-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-23\" data-attachment-id=\"653202\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195544/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-23.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-23/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195544/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-23-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eFor those seeking a more practical entry into classic rear-wheel drive performance car ownership, consider the Vauxhall Chevette HS and Talbot Sunbeam Lotus. Like the Renault 5 Turbo, these were homologation specials for Group 4 rallying, but they were already RWD from the get-go.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195614/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-30-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-30\" data-attachment-id=\"653209\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195614/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-30.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-30/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195614/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-30-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195631/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-34-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-34\" data-attachment-id=\"653213\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195631/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-34.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-34/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195631/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-34-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195618/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-31-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-31\" data-attachment-id=\"653210\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195618/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-31.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-31/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195618/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-31-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAs such, creating high-performance versions of the base cars didn’t compromise their practicality as family hatchbacks – though they were undeniably little hooligan machines.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195552/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-25-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-25\" data-attachment-id=\"653204\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195552/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-25.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-25/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195552/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-25-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195557/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-26-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-26\" data-attachment-id=\"653205\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195557/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-26.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-26/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195557/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-26-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195548/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-24-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-24\" data-attachment-id=\"653203\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195548/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-24.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-24/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195548/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-24-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Chevette HS featured an uprated 2.3-litre version of Vauxhall’s slant-four engine with twin Weber carburettors, while the Sunbeam’s 2.2-litre Lotus engine sported Dell’Orto carbs. The Talbot produced about 150hp, edging out the Chevette’s 135hp – high power for a small car in the late ’70s.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195627/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-33-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-33\" data-attachment-id=\"653212\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195627/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-33.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-33/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195627/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-33-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195606/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-28-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-28\" data-attachment-id=\"653207\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195606/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-28.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-28/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195606/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-28-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn Group 4 rally specification, both cars neared 250hp, which would have made them wild to hurl through forest roads lined with spectators. While Group B might be viewed as the pinnacle of rallying, the artistry of earlier RWD rally cars was something else altogether.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195601/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-27.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195601/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-27-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-27\" data-attachment-id=\"653206\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195601/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-27.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-27/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195601/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-27-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eTalbot and Lotus deserve special mention, too. The 1981 WRC championship marked the final year of Group 4 regulations, with Sunbeam clinching the manufacturer title ahead of Datsun and Ford. From 1982 onward, all-wheel drive dominance began, save for the legendary Lancia 037 in 1983.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195712/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-44.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195712/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-44-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-44\" data-attachment-id=\"653223\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195712/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-44.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-44/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195712/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-44-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063319/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-471-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-47\" data-attachment-id=\"653238\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063319/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-471.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-47-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063319/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-471-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195716/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-45-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-45\" data-attachment-id=\"653224\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195716/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-45.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-45/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195716/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-45-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195720/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-46-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-46\" data-attachment-id=\"653225\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195720/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-46.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-46/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195720/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-46-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eFast-forward to today, and the performance automotive landscape feels standardised and boring. Two-litre turbocharged automatic hot hatches and twin-turbo V8 super saloons are the norm, with most vehicles being AWD, quiet and hefty.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195640/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-36.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195640/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-36-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-36\" data-attachment-id=\"653215\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195640/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-36.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-36/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195640/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-36-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eEven supercars and hypercars have become uniform, electrified and bloated. One man became fed up with it all, and in August 2020, revealed a manual, sub-1,000kg (2,204lb) V12 supercar that revs beyond 12,000rpm and features functional ground effects thanks to its rear fan.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063329/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-491.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063329/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-491-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-49\" data-attachment-id=\"653240\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063329/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-491.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-49-2/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063329/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-491-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063346/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-52-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-52\" data-attachment-id=\"653244\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063346/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-52.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-52/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063346/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-52-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195656/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-40-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-40\" data-attachment-id=\"653219\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195656/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-40.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-40/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195656/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-40-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe man is Gordon Murray, and the car is his GMA T.50.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195652/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-39.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195652/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-39-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-39\" data-attachment-id=\"653218\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195652/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-39.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-39/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195652/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-39-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-48\" data-attachment-id=\"653239\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-48/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063343/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-53-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-53\" data-attachment-id=\"653243\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063343/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-53.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-53/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063343/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-53-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eI’d never seen a T.50 in person until October’s Sunday Scramble at Bicester Heritage, where\u003cem\u003e seven\u003c/em\u003e of these marvels were on display. While my passion leans towards ’90s tuning and motorsport, this particular pair stopped me dead in my tracks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195648/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-38-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-38\" data-attachment-id=\"653217\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195648/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-38.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-38/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195648/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-38-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063350/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-51-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-51\" data-attachment-id=\"653245\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063350/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-51.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-51/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063350/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-51-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063354/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-50-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-50\" data-attachment-id=\"653246\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063354/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-50.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-50/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063354/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-50-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s refreshing to see that we’re rising from the depths of automotive monotony, with modern technology and innovative thinking allowing creative minds to shine once more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195644/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-37.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195644/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-37-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-37\" data-attachment-id=\"653216\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195644/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-37.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-37/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195644/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-37-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195659/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-41-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-41\" data-attachment-id=\"653220\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195659/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-41.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-41/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195659/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-41-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195707/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-43-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-43\" data-attachment-id=\"653222\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195707/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-43.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-43/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/08195707/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-43-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhat stood out at this Bicester event wasn’t just the cars. The Scramble is more than a show; it’s a meet. These aren’t polished show ponies but real cars driven in on a crisp autumn morning.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"MC SS Pairs SH-48\" data-attachment-id=\"653239\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/exemplary-engineering-at-bicester-heritage-sunday-scramble/mc-ss-pairs-sh-48/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/09063324/MC-SS-Pairs-SH-48-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eLong live the engineers who design such remarkable machines, and long live the enthusiasts who relish \u003cem\u003edriving\u003c/em\u003e them!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMario Christou\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nInstagram: \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mcwpn\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emcwpn\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mariochristou.world\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emariochristou.world\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://mariochristou.world/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003emariochristou.world\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/tag/uk\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMore stories from the UK on Speedhunters\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
